contentrichtext.text: {{italic title}}<!-- This article was auto-generated by [[User:Polbot]]. --> {{Taxobox | name = Xenobatrachus anorbis | image = | status = DD | status_system = IUCN3.1 | regnum = [[Animalia]] | phylum = [[Chordata]] | classis = [[Amphibia]] | ordo = [[Frog|Anura]] | familia = [[Microhylidae]] | genus = ''[[Xenobatrachus]]'' | species = '''''X. anorbis''''' | binomial = ''Xenobatrachus anorbis'' | binomial_authority = Blum & Menzies, 1989 | synonyms = }} '''''Xenobatrachus anorbis''''' is a species of [[frog]] in the [[Microhylidae]] family. It is found in [[West Papua (region)|West Papua]] in [[Indonesia]] and [[Papua New Guinea]]. Its natural [[habitat]]s are subtropical or tropical moist [[montane forest]]s, [[swamp]]s, and rural gardens. It is threatened by [[habitat loss]]. ==Source== * Richards, S. & Price, D. 2004.
